// Based on symbols/us_intl keyboard map:
// Dead-keys definition for a very simple US/ASCII layout.
// by Conectiva (http://www.conectiva.com.br)
// modified by Ricardo Y. Igarashi (iga@that.com.br)

// Added the following deadkeys, to make it truly international:
//
// dead_macron: on AltGr-Shift-comma
// dead_breve: on AltGr-Shift-parenleft
// dead_abovedot: on AltGr-Shift-period
// dead_abovering: on AltGr-Shift-parenright
// dead_doubleacute: on AltGr-Shift-2
// dead_caron: on AltGr-Shift-5
// dead_cedilla: on AltGr-comma
// dead_ogonek: on AltGr-Shift-8
// dead_belowdot: on AltGr-period
// dead_hook: on AltGr-question (AltGr-Shift-slash)
// dead_horn: on AltGr-Shift-7
// dead_diaeresis: on AltGr-colon (Alt-shift-semicolon)
//
// those were already there:
// dead_grave: on AltGr-grave
// dead_acute: on AltGr-apostrophe
// dead_circumflex: on AltGr-Shift-6
// dead_tilde: on AltGr-tilde (AltGr-Shift-grave)
// dead_diaeresis: on AltGr-quotedbl (AltGr-Shift-apostrophe)

